<br>
For those that don't know, Majestic is a brand new game by EA that promises to revolutionize the face of interactive gaming. It gets your contact information (phone #, fax #, AIM sn, email addy) and computer generated characters contact you and push you into the plot. The game is supposedly about a conspiracy that you are trapped in, but very little of the actual plot has leaked from EA (kudos to the beta testers!). The game will apparently do crazy things like call your home at 11:00 at night with death threats if you explore a certain secure website further (you can specify times for the game to call you though, or turn off phone calls altogether). I've yet to play it very much, but it really looks AMAZING and will probably be talked about a lot in the upcoming months (it just came out today). If you guys want more info, the website is:<br>
